      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "AGATHA (1) resumes from a lengthy break. Finished off strongly on debut with a handy third over 1100m at this track last June. Fitted with the two trials and expect to see her race a touch closer from the good gate. Tongue-tie goes on and gets every chance. ARTGIRL (2) showed a stack of potential in her first prep with a string of minor placings in town. Wasn't pushed out in her two trials and look for her late. MISS SUPERNOVA (4) resumes. Failed to close off when left in front with a fading fourth over 1200m at Warwick Farm on January 7. Kept up to the mark with a Rosehill trial placing over 900m. Gets her chance from the good gate. GIRL ABOUT TOWN (7) Tom Charlton trained two-year-old filly by Zousain from Miss promiscuity on debut. Has shown enough in the two trials to warrant serious consideration.",
